  <dt className="text-sm text-foreground-100/60">Status</dt>
  <dd className="text-sm font-medium">Active</dd>
</div>
```

## 9. Interactive States

**Principle:** Every interactive element needs clear state feedback.

**State Progression:**
```
Default  → Base appearance
Hover    → Subtle highlight (bg change, border darken)
Focus    → Clear ring (accessibility requirement)
Active   → Pressed appearance (darker, shifted)
Disabled → Reduced opacity, no pointer
```

**Example:**
```tsx
className="
  bg-accent-100 text-white
  hover:bg-accent-100/90
  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-accent-100/50
  active:bg-accent-100/80
  disabled:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none
"
```

## 10. Progressive Disclosure

**Principle:** Show essential information first; reveal details on demand.

**Patterns:**
- Expandable sections with clear affordance
- Truncate long text with "Show more"
- Summary → Detail drill-down
- Tooltips for supplementary info

**Affordances:**
- Chevron icons indicate expandability
- "..." menus for additional actions
- Hover states reveal hidden controls

