## 20. Backdrop Blur & Glassmorphism

**Principle:** Overlays should retain visual context of what's beneath them, creating spatial continuity.

**Why Blur Matters:**
- Preserves awareness of underlying content
- Creates depth without full occlusion
- Associates the overlay with its origin context
- Feels lighter and more modern than opaque backgrounds

**Blur Patterns:**
```tsx
// Modal/dialog backdrop
<div className="fixed inset-0 bg-black/50 backdrop-blur-sm" />

// Floating panel (popover, dropdown)
<div className="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-xl shadow-2xl">

// Tooltip with subtle blur
<div className="rounded-lg bg-black/70 backdrop-blur-md px-3 py-2">

// Navigation bar (sticky)
<nav className="sticky top-0 border-b border-white/10 bg-background-100/80 backdrop-blur-lg">
```

**Blur Intensity Scale:**
```
backdrop-blur-sm   (4px)   → Subtle, for light overlays
backdrop-blur      (8px)   → Default, general purpose
backdrop-blur-md   (12px)  → Moderate, tooltips
backdrop-blur-lg   (16px)  → Strong, navigation
backdrop-blur-xl   (24px)  → Heavy, modals/popovers
backdrop-blur-2xl  (40px)  → Maximum, command palettes
```

**Glassmorphism Recipe (Dark Mode):**
```tsx
className={cn(
  // Semi-transparent background
  "bg-[#1a1a1a]/80",
  // Strong blur
  "backdrop-blur-xl",
  // Subtle border for edge definition
  "border border-white/10",
  // Soft shadow for lift
  "shadow-xl shadow-black/20",
  // Rounded corners
  "rounded-xl"
)}
```

**Glassmorphism Recipe (Light Mode):**
```tsx
className={cn(
  "bg-white/70",
  "backdrop-blur-xl",
  "border border-black/5",
  "shadow-lg shadow-black/5",
  "rounded-xl"
)}
```

**Rules:**
- Always pair blur with semi-transparent background (not fully opaque)
- Add subtle border to define edges against blurred content
- Test blur against varied backgrounds (light, dark, colorful)
- Consider performance: blur is GPU-intensive on large areas

## 21. Contextual Positioning & Anchoring

**Principle:** Overlays must appear anchored to their trigger, maintaining spatial relationship.

**Positioning Fundamentals:**
```
Trigger is the origin → Overlay appears relative to it
User's attention stays connected to source
Position adapts to available viewport space
```

**Common Anchor Positions:**
```
        top-start    top    top-end
              ┌───────────────┐
   left-start │               │ right-start
              │   [Trigger]   │
     left     │               │ right
              │               │
   left-end   │               │ right-end
              └───────────────┘
      bottom-start  bottom  bottom-end
```

**Implementation with Floating UI / Radix:**
```tsx
// Popover anchored to trigger
<Popover>
  <PopoverTrigger asChild>
    <Button>Open Menu</Button>
  </PopoverTrigger>
  <PopoverContent 
    align="start"           // Horizontal: start | center | end
    side="bottom"           // Vertical: top | bottom | left | right
    sideOffset={8}          // Gap from trigger (px)
    alignOffset={0}         // Alignment adjustment
    collisionPadding={16}   // Viewport edge padding
  >
    {/* Content */}
  </PopoverContent>
</Popover>
```

**Tooltip Positioning Rules:**
```
Mouse hover → Tooltip follows cursor or anchors to element
Button click → Popover anchors to button center/edge
Form field → Dropdown anchors to field, full width
Context menu → Appears at cursor position
```

**Detail Panels (Adjacent Context):**
```tsx
// When selection needs rich context, show detail panel alongside
<div className="flex">
  <ListPanel className="w-64">
    {items.map(item => (
      <ListItem 
        key={item.id}
        onHover={() => setHoveredItem(item)}  // Detail appears on hover
        onClick={() => setSelectedItem(item)} // Or on selection
      />
    ))}
  </ListPanel>
  
  {/* Detail panel appears adjacent, not overlapping */}
  {hoveredItem && (
    <DetailPanel className="w-80 border-l border-white/10">
      <ItemDetails item={hoveredItem} />
    </DetailPanel>
  )}
</div>
```

**Viewport Collision Handling:**
```tsx
// Flip to opposite side if not enough space
side="bottom"      // Preferred
avoidCollisions    // Auto-flip to top if needed

// Shift along axis to stay in viewport
<PopoverContent
  collisionBoundary={viewportRef}
  collisionPadding={16}
/>
```

**Animation & Transitions:**
```tsx
// Animate from anchor point for spatial continuity
className={cn(
  // Origin matches anchor position
  "origin-top-left",
  // Scale + fade in
  "data-[state=open]:animate-in data-[state=closed]:animate-out",
  "data-[state=open]:fade-in-0 data-[state=closed]:fade-out-0",
  "data-[state=open]:zoom-in-95 data-[state=closed]:zoom-out-95",
  // Slide from anchor direction
  "data-[side=bottom]:slide-in-from-top-2",
  "data-[side=top]:slide-in-from-bottom-2"
)}
```

**Rules:**
- Overlay should never cover its trigger (user loses context)
- Maintain 4-8px gap between trigger and overlay
- Prefer bottom/right positioning (follows reading direction)
- Always handle viewport edges gracefully (flip/shift)
- Animate from the anchor point, not center of screen

